# LiDAR SLAM TurtleBot3 Workspace Notes

[Back to the repository README](../../README.md)

## Purpose

This workspace path collects ROS2-oriented LiDAR, SLAM, TurtleBot3, and navigation material. It is a development area, not proof of an end-to-end validated robot stack.

## Maturity

**Pending Validation / ROS2 Environment Required.** A complete clean-checkout build, launch sequence, Gazebo run, Nav2 integration test, and hardware test have not been established by this document.

## Required validation

Before describing this workspace as operational, verify and record:

- the supported ROS2 distribution;
- package manifests and dependencies;
- `colcon` build results;
- launch-file and parameter paths;
- TF tree and topic compatibility;
- SLAM and localization behavior;
- Nav2 goal execution and recovery behavior;
- simulation provenance;
- hardware model, firmware, sensors, and calibration when applicable.

## Inspect the workspace

From the repository root:

```bash
find ros2_ws/lidar_slam_tb3 -maxdepth 4 -type f -print
```

## Limitations

- No formal safety or autonomous-operation guarantee is provided.
- Simulation-only evidence does not establish hardware readiness.
- The workspace may contain incomplete or archived components requiring further cleanup.
